Date: 0/0/1863
Source: First Year in Canterbury Settlement
Author: BUTLER
Vol / Page: ch vii 104
Edition:
Quote: In the small river Ashburton ... we had a little misunderstanding [105] with the bullocks; the leaders ... slewed sharply round, and tied themselves into an inextricable knot with the polars [sic], while the body bullocks by a manoeuvre not unfrequent, shifted, or as it is technically termed, slipped, the yoke under their necks, and the bows over; the off bullock, turning upon the near side, and the near bullock upon the off.
Notes: 1860 in 1863

